sec.p:
A total of 8 studies with 851 patients were included in this meta-analysis. The included studies were published from 1967 to 2008. The results of the retrieved studies are summarized in Table 1
. The prevalences in our meta-analysis ranged from 0 to 0.655. Looking at Table 1, we find variability between studies. Among patients with TAO, we find a group of studies that estimate a prevalence of RS between 0 and 0.1. Another group of studies show a prevalence ranging from 0.2 to 0.3. There are 3 outliers with high (0.438) and very high (0.5, 0.655) prevalences. This variability between the studies also becomes obvious when looking at a forest plot of the data, which shows the estimate prevalence together with a 95% CI (Figure 2
).
